POWER ARCHITECTURE

  Overview:
The RangeGuard system is powered from a **24V DC industrial supply**. A **TPS5403DR buck converter** efficiently steps the voltage down to **3.3V**, which serves as the main power rail for all onboard electronics.


  Power Tree


24V DC Input
      │
      ▼
 Fuse Protection
      │
      ▼
TPS5403DR Buck Converter
     (24V → 3.3V)
      │
      ├── PIC16F877A Microcontroller
      ├── VL53L0X ToF Sensor
      ├── ESP8266 Wi-Fi Module
      ├── microSD Card
      ├── MAX3232 RS-232 Interface
      └── Buzzer Driver Circuit




   Power Distribution

| Component     | Supply Voltage |
| ------------- | -------------: |
| PIC16F877A    |           3.3V |
| VL53L0X       |           3.3V |
| ESP8266       |           3.3V |
| microSD Card  |           3.3V |
| MAX3232       |           3.3V |
| Buzzer Driver |           3.3V |



   Estimated Current Consumption

| Component    |      Typical Current |
| ------------ | -------------------: |
| PIC16F877A   |               ~12 mA |
| VL53L0X      |               ~20 mA |
| ESP8266      | ~80 mA (300 mA Peak) |
| microSD Card |               ~50 mA |
| MAX3232      |                ~5 mA |
| Buzzer       |               ~30 mA |


   Overall Power Consumption

| Parameter                 | Value   |
| ------------------------- | ------- |
| Input Voltage             | 24V DC  |
| Output Voltage            | 3.3V DC |
| Typical Current           | ~170 mA |
| Peak Current              | ~475 mA |
| Typical Power             | ~0.55 W |
| Peak Power                | ~1.57 W |
| Buck Converter Efficiency | >90%    |



   Key Features

* 24V industrial power input
* High-efficiency TPS5403DR buck converter
* Single regulated 3.3V power rail
* Low power consumption
* Stable operation using decoupling capacitors
* Supports simultaneous sensing, logging, communication, and alarm generation
